From: Qiang Ma <maqianga@uniontech.com>
Date: Mon, 4 May 2026 09:00:37 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] LoongArch: KVM: Cap KVM_CAP_NR_VCPUS by KVM_CAP_MAX_VCPUS
References: bsc#1258210
Patch-mainline: 6.18.30
Git-commit: b3e31a6650d4cab63f0814c37c0b360372c6ee9e

commit b3e31a6650d4cab63f0814c37c0b360372c6ee9e upstream.

It doesn't make sense to return the recommended maximum number of vCPUs
which exceeds the maximum possible number of vCPUs.

Other architectures have already done this, such as commit 57a2e13ebdda
("KVM: MIPS: Cap KVM_CAP_NR_VCPUS by KVM_CAP_MAX_VCPUS")

Cc: stable@vger.kernel.org
Reviewed-by: Bibo Mao <maobibo@loongson.cn>
Signed-off-by: Qiang Ma <maqianga@uniontech.com>
Signed-off-by: Huacai Chen <chenhuacai@loongson.cn>
Signed-off-by: Greg Kroah-Hartman <gregkh@linuxfoundation.org>
Signed-off-by: Robert Frohl <rfrohl@suse.com>
---
 arch/loongarch/kvm/vm.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/arch/loongarch/kvm/vm.c b/arch/loongarch/kvm/vm.c
index 85246a70d95d..e86a32fffcdd 100644
--- a/arch/loongarch/kvm/vm.c
+++ b/arch/loongarch/kvm/vm.c
@@ -94,7 +94,7 @@ int kvm_vm_ioctl_check_extension(struct kvm *kvm, long ext)
 		r = 1;
 		break;
 	case KVM_CAP_NR_VCPUS:
-		r = num_online_cpus();
+		r = min_t(unsigned int, num_online_cpus(), KVM_MAX_VCPUS);
 		break;
 	case KVM_CAP_MAX_VCPUS:
 		r = KVM_MAX_VCPUS;
-- 
2.53.0

